Tanglin Shopping Centre is a 12-storey freehold retail and office development with 2 basement levels and a multi-storey carpark. 
It comprises shops and restaurants from levels B2 to 4, medical units from levels 4 to 6 and offices from levels 7 to 12. The multi-storey carpark is accessible from the main building via a link bridge.
Tanglin Shopping Centre is a stone’s throw away from the tourist/ shopping/ entertainment belt, along Orchard Road. The immediate vicinity is commercial in nature comprising hotels, shopping centers, and office developments. The building is also within close proximity to the luxury residential estates at Nassim Road and Ardmore Park. 
Public transportation is readily available along Tanglin Road. Within walking distance are the Orchard MRT station and the future Orchard Boulevard MRT station that is expected to be completed by the Year 2019.
Rare to find. Sale with vacant possession.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
GB Building is well served by rail, road and foot, within a 3-minute sheltered walk to Tanjong Pagar MRT Interchange and easily accessible via major expressways including Marina Coastal Expressway (MCE) and East Coast Park Expressway (ECP).
Tenants and visitors to the property can also enjoy the site’s proximity to a wide array of amenities including popular retail, F&B and lifestyle establishments at OUE Downtown and the vibrant Amoy Street area.
Notable developments in the vicinity include Asia Square, Frasers Tower, Capital Tower and the upcoming 79 Robinson Road and Afro-Asia I-Mark Building.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
As exclusive marketing agent, CBRE is pleased to present a rare chance to acquire prime office space in the heart of the Central Business District (CBD).  
Situated on levels 16 and 23 of GB Building, each floor has an exclusive lift lobby and boasts column free layouts for maximum design efficiency
This opportunity offers investors and owner-occupiers the chance to gain entry into Singapore’s tightly held CBD strata office market. With the site’s excellent connectivity and ongoing rejuvenation of the surrounding area, investors will also benefit from strong capital appreciation and rental upside in the future.
The sale will be conducted via an Expression of Interest (EOI) exercise which closes 28 July (Tuesday) at 3pm SGT.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE, as the exclusive marketing agent, is inviting offers through an Expression of Interest (EOI) exercise for the purchase of two contiguous 999-year leasehold office floors located at the prestigious Samsung Hub, a prime Grade A office building located in the heart of Singapore’s Central Business District (CBD). 
The building is a 30-storey office and retail development comprising office space from levels 8-30, retail units on the ground floor and carparking from levels 3-6.
The 9th and 10th floor comprises a total of eight strata-titles, representing a total strata area of 26,220 sq ft.
The consecutive floors and the provision of knock out panels further enhance interfloor connection via internal staircases.
Due to the quality of the building, Samsung Hub has attracted a number of multinational corporations and financial tenants not found in the majority of other
strata office buildings.Reputable tenants include Samsung Corporation, Saxo Capital Markets and Regus.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
Located along the Paya Lebar Road, Paya Lebar Square sits at the gateway of Singapore’s Eastern Commercial Hub, positioned close to the financial and business core of Singapore.

Paya Lebar is earmarked by the URA as a vibrant hub bringing work closer to homes and for companies to leapfrog into the international playing field. Several catalytic new projects and developments in the vicinity include Paya Lebar Quarters,
Singapore Post Centre, Park Place Residences etc.

Paya Lebar Square sits on top of Paya Lebar MRT Interchange and is also of walking distance to a multitude of conveniences and lifestyle amenities. Enjoying seamless connectivity to all parts of Singapore, Paya Lebar Square is conveniently located
with excellent accessibility to major expressways including Central Expressway (CTE), East Coast Parkway (ECP) and the Nicoll Highway.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
It is accessible through the nearest train stations such as Paya Lebar (CC9 EW8), Macpherson (CC10 DT26), and Eunos (EW7). The nearest primary schools are Geylang Methodist School (primary), Kong Hwa School, and Macpherson Primary School.

This property is close to amenities like Giant (Tanjong Katong Complex), Sheng Siong Hypermarket (Tanjong Katong), and Giant (Aljunied Avenue 2). The closest shopping malls are Paya Lebar Square, Paya Lebar Quarters, Singapore Post Centre, and City Plaza.
